<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>c. 1950-1960 &#8211; Business Card for Idlewild Lodge</strong></span>


<br>
Idlewild Business Card given out to guests. c. 1950-1960. The spelling of "Idle Wild" is used.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 



<br>
<i>"Mrs. L. L. Dauth, 113 18th St., Phone 1095-J, Greeley, Colo. ; Day-Weekly-Seasonal Rates; Idle Wild Lodge; 1 Blk. West of Trading Post; 15 Miles West of Loveland in Big Thompson Canon; Riding Horses Available; Mailing Address Idlewild Lodge - Drake Rt. Loveland, Colo.; Phone Cedar Cove No. 5"</i>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>People</strong></i></span> 
<br>






Anna Dauth


<br>



<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: c. 1950-1960</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>





<br>
<i>Source: Dauth Family Archive [USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild], c. 1950-1960</i>
<br>


