<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>c. 1950-1960 &#8211; Advertisement for Idlewild Lodge</strong></span>


<br>
An advertisement for Idlewild Lodge made by Anna Jeremiassen, wife of Leslie Dauth. c. 1950-1960. The spelling of "Idlewild" is used.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 



<br>
<i>""It's Springtime In The Rockies"; Spend a vacation in comfort at "IDLEWILD." Modern, electric lights, well furnished, good beds.; Riding Horses Available; REASONABLE RATES, By Week, Month, or Season. "Please Tell Your Friends!"; Write or Phone Mrs. Leslie Dauth; 1113 Eighteenth Street, Greeley, Colorado Phone 1095-J; Or Idlewild, Drake Route, Loveland, Colorado; Now Open For Reservation; Idlewild Lodge; 8 Miles Up Big Thompson Canon - 16 Miles From Loveland, Colo."</i>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>People</strong></i></span> 
<br>






Anna Dauth


<br>



<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: c. 1950-1960</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>





<br>
<i>Source: Dauth Family Archive [USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild], c. 1950-1960</i>
<br>


